To disable the form fields in the "daftar" blade based on the condition of the date being after the latest day of February, you can modify the edit function in your controller as follows:
[
use Carbon\Carbon;
]

public function edit($id = null)
{
    // Retrieve the $userData object using the DB::table() method.
    $userData = DB::table('petanibajak')
        ->where('nokp', Auth::user()->nokp)
        ->orderBy('tarpohon', 'desc')
        ->first();

    // Check if the date is after the latest day of February
    $disableForm = false;
    if ($userData) {
        $latestDayOfFebruary = Carbon::parse($userData->tarpohon)->endOfMonth()->startOfMonth()->addMonths(1)->subDay();
        if (Carbon::now()->gt($latestDayOfFebruary)) {
            $disableForm = true;
        }
    }

    // Then, the null coalescing operator (??) is used to assign the default object with null values if $userData is null.
    $userData = $userData ?? (object) [
        'nama' => null,
        'nokp' => null,
        'jantina' => null,
        'alamat' => null,
        'poskod' => null,
        'daerah' => null,
        'telrumah' => null,
        'telhp' => null,
        'nopetani' => null,
        'tahunpohon' => null,
        'baru' => null,
        'musim' => null,
        'musim2' => null,
        'stesen' => null,
        'tarpohon' => null,
    ];

    // Create a new variable to hold the formatted date value
    $tarikhMemohon = $userData ? Carbon::parse($userData->tarpohon)->toDateString() : '';

    return view('daftar', compact('userData', 'tarikhMemohon', 'disableForm'));
}
In the updated code:

-We added the use Carbon\Carbon; statement at the top to import the Carbon library for working with dates.
-We introduced a new variable $disableForm to hold the boolean value indicating whether the form fields should be disabled.
-Inside the condition where $userData is not null, we calculate the latest day of February based on the tarpohon value using Carbon methods.
-We compare the current date (Carbon::now()) with the latest day of February ($latestDayOfFebruary) using the gt() method to check if the current date is greater than the latest day of February.
-If the current date is greater, we set $disableForm to true to indicate that the form fields should be disabled.
-In the view, we pass the $disableForm variable to the "daftar" blade.
-In the "daftar" blade, you can use the $disableForm variable to conditionally disable the form fields using HTML attributes or JavaScript.
-For example, to disable the form fields using HTML attributes, you can add the disabled attribute to the form elements based on the value of $disableForm:

[
<input type="text" name="nama" value="{{ $userData->nama }}" {{ $disableForm ? 'disabled' : '' }}>
]

Make sure to adjust the code based on your specific requirements and form structure.

